&gt;  here are a few ideas:
&gt;  
&gt;  -It may just be that the population is taking up too much room with 
&gt;  big genomes.  You can try reducing the population size.  It really 
&gt;  doesn&#39;t have to be big to be effective.  Just remember that the 
&gt;  number of species should be roughly popsize/12. 
&gt;  
&gt;  -See the question on the NEAT Users Page FAQ: 
&gt;  &quot;NEAT takes up too much memory. Can I save memory somehow? &quot;
&gt;  It is aimed at my C++ code but I think the same principle can 
&gt;  probably be applied in JNEAT.
&gt;  
&gt;  -Use a memory monitor and figure out exactly when the memory is
&gt;  overflowing.  Is it right when the pop is created or does it 
&gt;  gradually build up over generations?
&gt;  
&gt;  -Try a computer with more memory. 
